            <title>[SPR-2608] AbstractAspectJAdvice and AspectJAroundAdvice subvert ReflectiveMethodInvocation.invocableClone</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2608</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using ReflectiveMethodInvocation.invocableClone in an @Around aspect to implement transaction retries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, AbstractAspectJAdvice &amp;amp; AspectJAroundAdvice stash a ProceedingJoinPoint in the MIs userAttributes.  That stashed PJP has a pointer to the original, uncloned, MI, so invoking my cloned MI ends up calling the next interceptor twice (because the interceptorIndex is coming from this stashed PJP/MI).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think a workaround is to just clear out the stashed PJP, but I haven&apos;t tried that yet.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
